The paper discusses the use of machine learning (specifically, reservoir computing) to emulate chaotic systems and synchronize them, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE) and dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of chaos in cryptography, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of reservoir computing in control systems, which falls under the category of control theory (cs.SY).
